        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Security Safe Deposit Company&#44;<lb/>
                &#34;Equitable Building&#44;&#34;<lb/>
                Corner Milk and Federal Streets.<lb/>
                Containing the elegant Reading Room and Ladies&#39; Apartments&#44;<lb/>
                in addition to the Vaults.<lb/></p>
            <p>Boston&#44; Tamuz 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5650<lb/></p>
            <p>&#91;Print of building&#93;<lb/> Rental of Safes from &#36;10 to &#36;100 per year.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi>. Dr. S. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>My very dear Doctor &#40;why kindly return<lb/> on Wednesday<lb/></p>
            <p>Enclosed is a letter we received from<lb/> Dr. Drachman&#39;s congregation which as far as I know is<lb/> correct &#40;but last Monday Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi>. M<hi rend="sup">r</hi>. Drachman came to<lb/> Boston&#44; instead of sending us the designs as I had asked<lb/> in reply to their letter and giving us the size of the Ark&#41;<lb/> he brought us up a sketch of an ark to be made in<lb/> oak to match the other fittings &#40;<hi rend="underline">but without the ten</hi><lb/>  <hi rend="underline">commandments</hi> &#38; curtains&#41; and what farther does not please me<lb/> they have the gallery built joining the ark &#40;for the choir&#41;<lb/> he stated that the ark would cost without curtains<lb/> &#38; Tablets &#40;1200&#41; I enclose hundred Dollars&#41; when<lb/> Dr. Drachman was here I promised if possibly my<lb/> son could meet the Architect in New York last<lb/> Sunday and get his ideas &#38; have one made here<lb/> I now would be glad if you will read over the<lb/> enclosed letter&#44; &#38; after approving of the same mail<lb/> it.  <sic>believe</sic> me my dearest Doctor my heart soul&#39;s is<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>for the advancement of our Holy Religion&#44; but as they<lb/> have built so grand a synagogue&#44; it puts me to think<lb/> the building will be mortgaged for &#36;40&#44;000 &#38; from the<lb/> most reliable authority I hear Dr. Drachman is to<lb/> receive a very large salary&#44; &#38; has been elected for life.<lb/>  When we made the offer we did so with the very best<lb/> intentions but never dreamt we would be dictated &#38;<lb/> forced to &#91;&#63;&#93; an Ark to suit its fittings as a<lb/> gift we thought we were to do what in our judgment<lb/> should be most suitable we have a large mat in<lb/> Jerusalem &#38; its our pride all the labour &#38; work should<lb/> be done in the Holy City &#40;the work which my agent has<lb/> done there is most beautiful&#44; and I feel confident it<lb/> will not cost including curtains Tablets&#44; freight &#38;<lb/> expenses over Eight hundred Dollars.<lb/></p>
            <p>The money donated by my darling daughter from the<lb/> Ticket we pray to God to give us knowledge but we<lb/> wish to divide equally around with the most<lb/> sincere &#38; kind wishes to you &#38; all dear you in<lb/> which my beloved daughter &#38; son join<lb/>  Remain <sic>your&#39;s</sic> faithfully<lb/> Alfred A Marcus<lb/></p>
            <p>We will send you by<lb/> tomorrow Express a few<lb/> photographs taken by Simeon my<lb/> son who is an Amateur never took a lesson &#38; only commenced about 10 months ago<lb/> please let us know if the Hebrew inscriptions are correct on the Synagogue<lb/></p>
            </body>
